      "title": "[New Atlas] 3D 'laser stirring' generates complex unobtainium-level alloys",
      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://assets.newatlas.com/dims4/default/cadddc1/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1727x907+0+193/resize/1200x630!/quality/85/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewatlas-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fce%2Fa4%2F86ab7efc4eb589f1e79da426f010%2Fscreenshot-2026-06-30-at-3-44-13-pm.png&amp;na.image_optimisation=0\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://assets.newatlas.com/dims4/default/cadddc1/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1727x907+0+193/resize/1200x630!/quality/85/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewatlas-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fce%2Fa4%2F86ab7efc4eb589f1e79da426f010%2Fscreenshot-2026-06-30-at-3-44-13-pm.png&amp;na.image_optimisation=0\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://assets.newatlas.com/dims4/default/cadddc1/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1727x907+0+193/resize/1200x630!/quality/85/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewatlas-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fce%2Fa4%2F86ab7efc4eb589f1e79da426f010%2Fscreenshot-2026-06-30-at-3-44-13-pm.png&amp;na.image_optimisation=0\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://assets.newatlas.com/dims4/default/cadddc1/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1727x907+0+193/resize/1200x630!/quality/85/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewatlas-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fce%2Fa4%2F86ab7efc4eb589f1e79da426f010%2Fscreenshot-2026-06-30-at-3-44-13-pm.png&amp;na.image_optimisation=0\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://assets.newatlas.com/dims4/default/cadddc1/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1727x907+0+193/resize/1200x630!/quality/85/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewatlas-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fce%2Fa4%2F86ab7efc4eb589f1e79da426f010%2Fscreenshot-2026-06-30-at-3-44-13-pm.png&amp;na.image_optimisation=0\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<p><img alt=\"Metal 3D printers, like this one at RPM Innovations’ facility, could become a whole lot more flexible in terms of using high-performance alloys\" src=\"https://assets.newatlas.com/dims4/default/8b1a286/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1727x1293+0+0/resize/1282x960!/format/webp/quality/85/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewatlas-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fce%2Fa4%2F86ab7efc4eb589f1e79da426f010%2Fscreenshot-2026-06-30-at-3-44-13-pm.png\" /><p>High-entropy alloys (HEAs) are metallurgy’s version of having your cake and eating it too, combining multiple elements to create unusual mixes of desirable properties. The problem is that they can be difficult to create, requiring proper mixing of the constituent elements at the atomic level.</p><p><a href=\"https://newatlas.com/materials/3d-printing-technique-high-entropy-alloy/\">Continue Reading</a></p><p><b>Category:</b> <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/materials/\">Materials</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/engineering/\">Engineering</a></p><p><b>Tags:</b> <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/3d-printing/\" rel=\"tag\">3D Printing</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/nist/\" rel=\"tag\">NIST</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/metals/\" rel=\"tag\">Metals</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/alloy/\" rel=\"tag\">Alloy</a></p>",
